<TEXT>After having my first accident with another type of car, I was particularly interested in a safe vehicle while still trying not to go over budget. I finally decided on a Kia Sportage and I think I made one of the best choices in a car that I have ever made. It has a 5 star rating, and it was not bad on my budget while I feel that I got a decent small SUV with a good warranty for my money. It has averaged about 22-23 mpg overall, but that is not bad compared to other SUV's on the market at the moment. I have three other family members who are buying Kia's now, although they all opted for the Amanti. My little SUV handles great and I drive an avg of 700 miles per week.</TEXT>
