<AUTHOR>rogerdar</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>I researched several small suvs and decided on the Sportage. It is very nimble in curvy mountain driving, and excellent in climbing grades with the alternate manual shift feature. It gets excellent mileage for a 6 cylinder car (20 around town; 25 on the highway at 70 mph), and cruises well on long distance drives. While there is some road noise on some road surfaces, it is not a major problem. I recently had to move quite a few large boxes and was able to accommodate them in the vehicle with all but the driver's seat laid flat. A nice feature.</TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Lay flat seats, including the front passenger seat. Easy access to all controls. The manual shift option for hill climbs and descents. </FAVORITE>
